            <p>
                I can agree with the most in this article, but with a different view at it, which might lead to a slightly different conclusion, or better said, to another feeling.&#xD;<br/>If you were a part of Rosia, then you are in the Kremlin always seen as a property of Moscow, even your offspring and the offspring of your offspring.&#xD;<br/>So, the surnames Khrushchev and Gorbachev are in their origin Ukrainian, and as a property of Moscow they have them suffixed with -ev (-ov), as a label of the totalitarian ruler (khan). In case of Gorbachev, they have the original consonant -H- changed into the Churchy-Cyrillic influenced -G-, which comes from the Latin script language. Thus, Khrushchev comes from Chrushch (&#x425;&#x440;&#x443;&#x449;), and Gorbachov from Horbach (&#x413;&#x43E;&#x440;&#x431;&#x430;&#x447;), likely from Horbatyy. Surnames might in Ukrainian also be adjective based like &#x425;&#x440;&#x443;&#x449;&#x456;&#x432;(&#x441;&#x44C;&#x43A;&#x438;&#x439;).&#xD;<br/>So, in Moscow, they see, at least Alaska and California always as part of Rosia, which was created as a result of the so-called Mongolian Storm, which you can also understand as a long-term occupation of the Silk Road.&#xD;<br/>In Rosia hasn&#x2019;t existed a class with rights. Even the nobility was the property of the czar without any rights. In Europe has as well existed serfdom, but the ruler wasn&#x2019;t such absolute.&#xD;<br/>Therefore, it is a difference between, allegedly, the same appearance in Europe and in Moscow. The communism was in Europe more a logical result of the Industrial Revolution.  The October Revolution in Moscow is based on the old feudalism, like the communist ruling in China. That&#x2019;s why it is so gruesome, and so alien to us.&#xD;<br/>Thus, the hope of a different outcome by an appearance of an US-Putin has a solid base.&#xD;<br/>But what might be a greater obstacle, as seen in the view of the author Khrushcheva, that the Republicans could be far more penetrated as it might seem. Maybe as a result, that Putin sells himself now as a &#x201C;white Russian&#x201D;, so a Bolshevik under a capitalist&#x2019;s top hat, so the Republicans don&#x2019;t see any more the red rag in the arena.&#xD;<br/>You see, if today&#x2019;s not so popular leaders of the Republicans declare openly to vote for Clinton, then the anticipation, why they do so, might be NOT so honorable. Even if the Koch Brothers fight allegedly against Trump, but have in mind, that the Koch Brothers are also, if not more, concerned about the Republican majority in both Houses&#x2026; It wonders not, that the Koch Brothers have a family affair with Stalin, you might say.&#xD;<br/>And here might the branching point, why we have had a Hitler, and now a Putin, might us direct towards the history of the US. After Yeltsin, the power system in Rosia hasn&#x2019;t had a winning candidate, and it has come to Putin.&#xD;<br/>At this point, the risk rather doesn&#x2019;t come directly from Trump, but from the changes in the open society of the USA, like U.S. Department of Homeland Security, even the necessity of naked scanners&#x2026; Which might at the end&#x2026;&#xD;<br/>---&#xD;<br/>The English proper name Russia = correlates to the old European-Ukrainian state Rus&#x2019; / &#x420;&#x443;&#x441;&#x44C;, which was destroyed from the Mongolian Storm. By the Mongolian Storm was created the Moscowian empire, which has become its proper name Rosia from a Byzantine word. Byzantium has Europe seen as a source of slaves, and Moscow sees itself as a successor of the Byzantine Empire.&#xD;<br/>The proper name Rus&#x2019; might itself have yet an Byzantine influence, and comes rather from the form Ruthenia, which has survived in Latin scriptures and in the Ukrainian language. The Ukrainian national emblem Trident is on the Easter eggs called Ruta. Ruta means in the first place rhomb, and is akin with the English word rhomb and the German word Raute. The Easter eggs stand for fertility. So, in those times were the Ukrainians such fertile like the rhombs by the rivers ~:{)&#xD;<br/>
            </p>
