<li class="comment " data-line-id="">
    <article class="comment__item" data-comment-id="59a7096c1d12552908c72251" data-comment-author="david-tavadian" itemprop="comment" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Comment">
        <header>
            <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
                <a href="/profile/david-tavadian" class="nmd-item__name"><span itemprop="name">David Tavadian</span></a>
            </span>
            &nbsp;<time itemprop="datePublished" datetime="2016-09-27T22:21Z">Sep 27, 2016</time>
        </header>
        <div itemprop="text">
            <p>
                Nina used Lenin as a reference. Why doesn&#x27;t she mention the fact that many of Hillary&#x27;s supporters are left of even Lenin? &#xD;<br/>&#xD;<br/>Russia was headed for a complete disintegration by the end of 1990s. Everything was set in motion for that to happen. Chechnya would separate, then Tatarstan, then Inigushetia.... and so on. That was the plan. Whose plan? I will let you figure it out.&#xD;<br/>&#xD;<br/>Then comes along Putin, from nowhere. He takes over the FSB, improves that organisation and gets of a lot of classified material. Then he becomes president and prevents Russia from disintegrating.&#xD;<br/>&#xD;<br/>Crimea was given away by Khrushchev, Nina&#x27;s grandfather. So Putin is effectively correcting Khrushchev&#x27;s mistakes.&#xD;<br/>&#xD;<br/>Nina sounds as confident in her unsubstantiated and arrogant opinions as Khrushchev was when he gave away Crimea, when he destroyed the agricultural sector with his idiotic reforms, and when he nearly destroyed the world with his lunatic foreign policy.&#xD;<br/>&#xD;<br/>Now, a few decades later, Khrushchev&#x27;s grand-daughter is telling other Americans whom they should elect. This overconfidence must be genetic.
            </p>
        </div>

            <button class="comment__reply u-hidden" aria-controls="comment__new__controls" aria-expanded="false">Reply</button>

    </article>

    

    <ul class="list list--indented u-hidden" data-id="cr-">
    </ul>
    <div class="comment__reply-refresh u-hidden">
        A new reply to this comment has been posted.&nbsp;<button>Load?</button>
